James Luke Ede (born 19 September 1984) is an English cricketer. Ede is a right-handed batsman who bowls right-arm medium pace. He was born at Burton-on-Trent, Staffordshire.
Ede played a single List-A match for the Derbyshire Cricket Board in the 1st round of the 2003 Cheltenham & Gloucester Trophy against the Middlesex Cricket Board, a match which was played in 2002.  During the match he scored 10 runs and took a single wicket, that of Rajesh Rao.In local domestic cricket, Ede plays for Quarndon Cricket Club who play in the Derbyshire Premier Cricket League.
